---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';

const updated = 'June 2026';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy · cusprose"
  path="/privacy/"
  description="How cusprose collects, uses, and protects your information."
>
  <Nav />

  <main class="prose">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="prose-hero">
        <p class="eyebrow"><span class="star">✦</span> LEGAL</p>
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="updated">Last updated: {updated}</p>
      </header>

      <section>
        <h2>1. Information we collect</h2>
        <p>
          We collect the information you provide directly — such as birth details
          you enter for a chart reading — and basic, anonymized analytics about
          how the Service is used.
        </p>

        <h2>2. How we use information</h2>
        <p>
          We use your information to generate readings, improve the Service, and
          maintain security. We do not sell your personal information.
        </p>

        <h2>3. Cookies &amp; analytics</h2>
        <p>
          cusprose may use cookies and privacy-respecting analytics to understand
          aggregate usage. You can control cookies through your browser settings.
        </p>

        <h2>4. Data retention</h2>
        <p>
          We retain information only as long as necessary to provide the Service
          and meet legal obligations.
        </p>

        <h2>5. Your rights</h2>
        <p>
          You may request access to, correction of, or deletion of your personal
          information by contacting us.
        </p>

        <h2>6. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Privacy questions? Email
          <a href="mailto:hello@cusprose.com">hello@cusprose.com</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Advertising &amp; third-party cookies</h2>
        <p>
          cusprose may display advertisements served by Google AdSense or other
          third-party advertising partners. These services may use cookies,
          web beacons, or similar technologies to collect information about your
          browsing activity across websites in order to provide relevant
          advertisements.
        </p>
        <p>
          Google's use of advertising cookies enables it and its partners to serve
          ads based on your visits to cusprose and other websites on the Internet.
          You may opt out of personalized advertising by visiting
          <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Ads Settings</a>.
          Alternatively, you can opt out of third-party vendor cookies by visiting
          <a href="https://optout.aboutads.info/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">aboutads.info</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>8. Regional privacy rights</h2>
        <p>
          If you are located in the European Economic Area (EEA), United Kingdom,
          or Switzerland, you have rights under the General Data Protection
          Regulation (GDPR), including the right to access, correct, delete, or
          restrict processing of your personal data, and the right to data
          portability.
        </p>
        <p>
          If you are a California resident, the California Consumer Privacy Act
          (CCPA) grants you the right to know what personal information we collect,
          the right to request deletion, and the right to opt out of the sale of
          your personal information. We do not sell personal information.
        </p>
        <p>
          To exercise any of these rights, contact us at
          <a href="mailto:hello@cusprose.com">hello@cusprose.com</a>.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .prose { padding-bottom: 5rem; }
  .prose-hero { max-width: 720px; margin: 1rem 0 2.5rem; }
  .prose-hero h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 4.5vw, 3.4rem);
    font-weight: 500;
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    margin: 1rem 0 0.75rem;
  }
  .updated {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
  }
  section { max-width: 720px; }
  h2 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin: 2rem 0 0.6rem;
  }
  p { color: var(--ink-soft); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  a { color: var(--gold); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 3px; }
</style>
